The global alosetron market is expected to witness significant growth by 2028, driven by the rising prevalence of irritable bowel syndrome and chronic diarrhea. The market segmentation based on indication includes irritable bowel syndrome (IBS-D) and chronic diarrhea. IBS-D accounts for a substantial portion of the market share due to the increasing cases of IBS globally. Chronic diarrhea is another important segment fueled by factors such as changing lifestyles, dietary habits, and increasing stress levels, leading to digestive disorders.

When it comes to the distribution channel, the market is segmented into hospital pharmacies, retail pharmacies, and online pharmacies. Hospital pharmacies play a crucial role in the distribution of alosetron due to the requirement of prescription drugs for the treatment of IBS-D and chronic diarrhea. Retail pharmacies are also significant contributors to the market as they cater to the increasing demand for over-the-counter medications. The online pharmacies segment is expected to witness rapid growth owing to the convenience and accessibility they offer to consumers in purchasing medications.

